itemListElement.name: 4-Day Yellowstone National Park, Spokane, Coeur d Alene Tour from Seattle

name: 4-Day Yellowstone National Park, Spokane, Coeur d Alene Tour from Seattle
description:
1. Exclusive 4-day wise tour to Yellowstone National Park, save money and time!

2. Experience the world’s longest floating boardwalk at Coeur D’Alene

3. Enjoy your leisure time

Attractions Notes: 

(1) Itinerary will be subject to traffic and weather. The sequence of the attractions might be changed according to actual and practical situation for better service. 

(2) In case of attraction closures (due to holidays or construction, etc.), tour guide may make some necessary changes to the itinerary accordingly. 

(3) “Attraction Admission” Yellowstone National Park $45/person (Required) for admission, parking, vehicle wear and fuel surcharges. 

(4) This tour does not accept any City Pass or your own tickets for the attraction. Guests need to purchase admission tickets from tour guides.

name: 2-Day Rainier & Olympic Park Tour
description:
Go to Mt. Rainier to see the tallest volcano of the continental United States by visiting Christine Falls, Narada Falls, and Paradise Road.

We take you to visit Olympic National Park with visiting Hurricane Ridge, Lake Crescent and many other great wonders of the natural beauty.

Additional Notice:

1. The tour guide might change the duration for each stop depending on weather conditions or others.

2. The tickets fee should pay to the tour guide in cash and the tour guide will arrange activities admissions for the group. City Passes and Annual passes are not acceptable on our tours.

3. All meals and drinks during the trip are not included. The tour guide will provide eating suggestions.

itemListElement.name: Food Walking Tours with Seattle Cultural Food Tours

name: Food Walking Tours with Seattle Cultural Food Tours
description: Eat what the locals on a food walking tour in one of Seattle’s diverse neighborhoods with the most authentic foods. Taste the love on a food journey like the historic Columbia City’s restaurant row with preserved buildings dating back to 1890. Immersive and historic food walking tours where eating is discovering culture!

review.name: Columbia City Food Walking Tour
review.reviewBody: We did this tour and had a ball.  Great food, info, and friends.  Angela did a fantastic job.  The farmers market was amazing.

name: Vacation Photographer in Seattle
description:
Localgrapher is the largest network of professional photographers and videographers with more than 600 destinations around the globe! Book your private photographer and guide in Seattle to capture your picture-perfect moments while visiting amazing sites!

SOLO TRAVELERS

Fancy an insta-perfect photoshoot from your Seattle vacation? Localgrapher has years of experience with fashion and solo travel photography! Make your memories last a lifetime and share them on social media or display them in your home to receive an avalanche of compliments. 

COUPLES

If you are about to propose to your loved one, honeymooning or just exploring what Seattle has to offer, put the selfie stick aside and let Localgrapher’s superb photographers take care of the photos for you both.

FAMILIES & GROUPS

A family trip, wedding, bachelorette party or grand get-together? Forget missing someone from pictures, we’ll capture them all!

itemListElement.name: Mt Rainier Private Tour Experience in SUV

name: Mt Rainier Private Tour Experience in SUV
description: Visit Mount Rainier National Park on this full-day tour. See waterfalls, old-growth forests, flowering meadows, and wildlife in their natural habitat. This experience on Mount Rainier makes your expected stops — but also ventures off the beaten path, with fantastic views and vistas, waterfalls, and park grounds. Walk or don't walk, you get the option. This tour travels all the way around Mount Rainier, and the different landscapes are fantastic. Four stops for trail walks and/or waterfalls are included.  May, June and late Oct, may have snow at Paradise, roads will be clear, but may need to return same route, and we've added extra walks if this happens.

review.name: Amazing!
review.reviewBody: Wonderful tour!! Cheryl was super!! Really listened to what we wanted and gave us all of it and more!!!! She had a water bottle for both of us (that we got to keep) and perfect snacks!! Cheryl has incredible knowledge of the area! We learned so much!! She also knows the best parking spots!!! My husband and I would have walked a mile before hiking and she just pulled up in crowded areas and found perfect spots!!! Thank you!!! If we are ever back in the area, we will do another one of your many options!!

review.name: This is a MUST when visiting Seattle!
review.reviewBody: Cheryl was a fantastic tour guide!  She was kind, courteous and knowledgable of all things Seattle and the Mt. Rainier National Park.  My wife and I were travelling with our two children (6 and 9yrs old) and we all had such a wonderful day with Cheryl.   She showed us all of the sites and sounds of the beautiful National Park.  We highly recommend her and we will absolutely be contacting her again when we revisit Seattle.  Thanks again for all of the memories!

review.name: A Phenomal Tour of Seattle with a Delightful Tour Guide and Magnificent Hospitality!
review.reviewBody:
Cheryl took us not only to Mount Rainier (Longmire Trail of the Shadows, Christine Falls, Narada Falls, Nisqually Glacier Trail, Reflection Lakes, and Silver Falls)
 but Snoqualmie Falls, Deception Falls, Leavenworth, Cascade Mountains, Deception Pass State Park, and Whidbey Island. It was a great experience with her heartwarming personality and her spacious and luxurious SUV. Her attitude to take us everywhere was very charming and she would also hike with us. If you ever want to take a memorable and astounding tour of Seattle, I highly recommend Cheryl for you!

review.name: Great Day with Awesome Views
review.reviewBody: Cheryl planned a variety of stops for our tour enabling us to see native trees, flowers, waterfalls and of course the Mt. Rainier summit. She was very knowledgeable and provided great information. She also adjusted our hikes to accommodate my sometimes troublesome knees. We had a great day.

review.name: Best private Mt Rainier tour-Great Experience!
review.reviewBody: Cheryl was a great guide and we thoroughly enjoyed the Mt Rainier tour. She customizes each tour to your preference and abilities for hiking the different trails and if you'd rather do a picnic lunch or a restaurant meal. She's very knowledgeable about the history and geography of the area which we luved learning about. It's great going with someone local who knows where all the restrooms and water refill stations are AND the secret picnic spot with a beautiful view of the mountain! She also provides some snacks and really nice reusable water bottle that you get to keep. If we ever make it back to the ared we will definitely come back for another tour.

review.name: If you’re looking to experience nature……
review.reviewBody: We spent a lovely day with Cheryl, she was very friendly and customised our tour to suit our needs. We saw all of the sights and Cheryl was full of information regarding Mount Rainier, the surroundings and the history of the area. We stopped at a small restaurant for lunch, the experience could have been better, but that was beyond Cheryl’s control. It was a wonderful day out in nature with the trees, wildlife and powerful waterfalls. Cheryl was great!!!

review.name: Mt Rainier is a must go
review.reviewBody:
I chose private tour because I'm a single mom traveling with a 10-year-old and a 7-year-old.  I didn't want to deal with driving, and I need something tailored to our needs.

Cheryl is native to this area.  She is very knowledgeable.  We had great conversation along the way (it was a long drive by the way).  She gave me lots of great ideas visiting in Seattle where we could get around with public transportation by ourselves.

She was very considerate, making multiple stops for young kids, trying to balance between fun and educational, brining a cooler so that we could get lunch on the way (restaurant at the park was not fully operating yet).  The SUV was clean and conffy.  And she is a safe driver.   She did not choose the shortest route to get to the destination, instead she took the one with more to see, and better sceneries.  I can tell Cheryl did her best to give us a good time.

review.name: Cheryl made the Mt Rainer trip one of the best excursions that we have done
review.reviewBody:
Cheryl at Northwest Adventures was wonderful. She was entertaining professional.
She took us to many wonderful spots in Mt Rainer. I feel I made a friend that day as she treated us like family. Cheryl was knowledgeable and familiar with the insight about the various routes, trails and sites.

review.name: Great Tour!
review.reviewBody: Cheryl is a lovely, informed, and kind person, who also happens to run a tour service. She provided our family of 4 with an amazing tour of Ranier that included several short hikes, views stops, and lots of information about what we were seeing along the way. She is great, and a tour with her is even better! Enjoy!

review.name: Outstanding experience!
review.reviewBody: An absolute pleasure. It felt like going with a friend and not a tour guide. Cheryl was knowledgeable and shared facts in a fun way. When we had to rearrange our route due to road closure, there were plenty of alternatives to chose from. The views were out of this world. Don't hesitate to book, or email Cheryl if you want adjustments to a specific tour. Will book again when we come back.

name: Temperate Rainforest Olympic Mountains
description:
Private tour.

This is a full day tour via our comfortable SUV to see a temperate rain forest and walk easy paths if you wish. Not required.  There are two trails, a lunch break, and you'll see the world's largest spruce tree. If you want we'll also take you to the Pacific Ocean. Customizable.

review.name: Fantastic Tour
review.reviewBody:
What a grand day we had in the Quinault Rainforest hiking and taking pictures of the beautiful green surroundings.  We took many photos it will be hard to choose favorites. We were very impressed with Cheryl's knowledge of the different plants, trees and history of the areas she took us to. She was very willing to accommodate us in every way. We would highly recommend Cheryl to anyone who wants to tour the Pacific North West.
Linda & Bill M

address.streetAddress: 1800 9th Ave In the Lobby of the 1800 9th Building
2045 2nd Ave Corner of Second and Lenora

name: Wacky Walks Walk About Scavenger Hunts

itemListElement.name: Hiking Tour to Mountain Peaks Alpine Lakes Rushing Waterfalls

name: Hiking Tour to Mountain Peaks Alpine Lakes Rushing Waterfalls
description:
We make exploring the PNW easy! Emily, our primary guide, will take great care of you. She will keep you safe, teach you about the Cascade Mountain Range, and will cheer you on as you accomplish a great workout. Emily is trained in CPR and Wilderness First Aid, she has hiked all around the PNW and the world (Patagonia and Mount Kilimanjaro...), and she is passionate about conservation. 

In addition to a great guide, you'll also get access to needed hiking gear! For the hike, you will get a backpack filled with the ten-essentials (key hiking safety items), comfort items, snacks, and water. 

All transportation is included. 

All you need to bring is your sense of adventure! A camera, sunglasses, and hiking boots are also strongly recommended.

review.name: Beautiful lake, waterfalls and trees and a brilliant guide!
review.reviewBody: We had a fantastic day with Emily visiting the stunningly beautiful Lake Twenty Two. The weather was not on our side but I thoroughly enjoyed our hike up to this incredibly stunning lake. Emily added all those touches to our day trip - hot drinks in the car and a full packed lunch with snacks. She also helped us identify different plant and fungi species along our route which just made this even more enjoyable. Emily also helped me celebrate my friends birthday with a little cake to celebrate which really added the final touch to our amazing day out.

review.name: Perfect dayhike to Lake 22
review.reviewBody: This was a perfect day hiking up to and around Lake 22. Emily did a smashing job as our tourguide. Knowledgable, pleasant, adjusting to our experience and wishes. Very good food and snacks. We experienced the first snow of the season.

review.name: Fantastic hike, highly recommend!
review.reviewBody: Emily is very thorough about what type of hike will suit best for you based on your hiking experience and what would you like to see. Emily is an experienced hiker with great knowledge about Seattle and different plant life on your hike. Also, the views during the hike are well worth the trip!

review.name: Great hike with a an awesome guide.
review.reviewBody: Emily is an awesome guide. Very easy to talk to,  knowledgeable of the area,  and she gave us recommendations for things to do while in Seattle.  She tailored the hike to our experience level and took us to a beautiful lake with a mountain  backdrop.  We had a great time and will book with Emily again when we make our way back to the area.

review.name: Great hike, tailored to our interests, small local business owner
review.reviewBody:
I was looking for a day-hike that we could do while staying in downtown Seattle and this was the perfect choice! Emily contacted us when we scheduled the hike to find out what our interests were. She picked us up at our hotel, with coffee and muffins, then we drove out to the hike. She also packed a nice lunch for the hike. The whole hike was tailored to our interests plus Emily has a wealth of knowledge about Seattle fauna that she shared throughout. 

Before booking I read another review that said hiking with Emily immediately feels like you’re on a hike with a friend and that’s 100% true. I’d definitely recommend this hike! (In fact, I already have to some folks on the way to our next destination!) 

Finally, I was glad to be able to support a small local business while exploring Seattle! It’s a great way to support the local economy while learning from a Seattle native.

review.name: The best ever hiking experience on the Pacific Northwest
review.reviewBody:
Emily is such an amazing guide and person to go in a hike with. I came across her guide by chance on TripAdvisor and have no regrets going on a solo hike with her.

Emily is meticulous about her work, and will plan a hike for you based on your preferences as well as skill level. She brought me up for a private hike up Wallace falls and as a beginner to hiking, it was the perfect setup and place to start my adventure in the Pacific Northwest. Plus, Emily is an experienced hiker so you can count on her to get all the hiking preparation needed and safety measures sorted out so that you can enjoy your hike without worry.

I was also pleasantly surprised by the direct pickup and drop-off at my hotel, as well as the breakfast and coffee that she prepared for me prior to the hike. It just goes to show how thoughtful she is with every single part of the process.

Were I to return to Seattle, I'm definitely booking her again for another hiking trip, and I give her my highest recommendation to all who are reading this. Choose Emily, for she is the best guide that you can get! :)

review.name: A beautiful and amazing hike in the Pnw!
review.reviewBody:
A wonderful experience of hiking in the pacific north west with Emily, and we were also fortunate to have Emily’s mum on the hike with us to. We also were joined by a couple too. The small group was perfect. 

The scenery and places to  hike in Seattle speak for them selves and I really wanted to Experience some of it.

Emily’s attention to detail was amazing!  
*in dialogue to see what experience you have and what type of hike you would like and uses that to give you several options to chose from!

I was picked up from my hotel and dropped off there too which was great and Emily was very punctual!  Herself and her mum were very engaging, polite and kind! 

Emily provided equipment for the hike if you wish to use it, a prepared back pack with a lunch, essentials to keep us safe!  Also had some muffins/coffee and water during the commute in the morning!

The hike was done to the pace that we wanted and felt comfortable with! We never felt rushed, Emily had so much knowledge and stories and facts about the places we were going, also shared cool places to go see in the city of Seattle. 

What I also enjoyed during this hike was the passion Emily has for the outdoors and travelling. It made for a very enjoyable chat whilst hiking.

I would 100 percent recommend booking a hike in the PNW with Emily.

review.name: True local hiking guide
review.reviewBody: I stumbled upon Emily's listing and I am so happy I did. Emily is the real deal, a true local hiking guide that know her way around. We got lucky with perfect weather going hiking in mid-November. Emily had the full setup, picked us up from our hotel as promised and on time. Had a smooth ride and a wonderful day trip, all with a personal touch. Highly recommended! Thank you so much.

review.name: 5 Star Tour Guide
review.reviewBody: Really enjoyed this beautiful hike! Our tour guide Emily was friendly, prepared, and super knowledgeable. You can tell that Emily is well experienced, she makes you feel comfortable and creates a great hiking experience.

review.name: Exactly what I was looking for!
review.reviewBody: Emily was a really wonderful tour guide. She and her mom gave me a private hike up to Lake 22.  It was the perfect little taste of the Pacific Northwest outdoors I was hoping for.  We started really early (7am!) but it was worth it because we beat the crowds on the hike, got parking, and made it back by 2pm so I had the rest of the day to do other stuff. Her planning and attention to details paid off.  The views were gorgeous and I got lots of great pictures I will cherish.  The hike was not too strenuous but it definitely got my heart rate up.  I appreciated that Emily paid close attention to what I wanted to do on the hike and thought of every possible way to ensure I was comfortable and enjoying the experience.  Emily is a young entrepreneur who is turning her passion for the outdoors into a small business so learning this made me even happier I chose to book the hike with her.  I highly recommend you consider booking her for your next PNW excursion.

name: Seattle Urban Wine Tours
description: You are guided through four tasting rooms of Washington Wines. Three wines are produced on site and if possible, the tour will get to visit with the winemakers.

itemListElement.name: Georgetown Neighborhood and Alki Beach Tour: historic, funky and beautiful!

name: Georgetown Neighborhood and Alki Beach Tour: historic, funky and beautiful!
description: This tour highlights a neighborhood most travelers miss when they visit, and it's a very unique slice of old Seattle that still survives. It's a time machine! After we explore Georgetown, we will visit Alki Beach, a local favorite with stunning views of Elliott Bay, Bainbridge Island and the Olympic Mountains. We may even spot a sea lion, a harbor porpoise, an eagle or an Orca on Alki, you never know. Come explore with a local of 30 years and get an insider's view of what life in Seattle is like for those of us that call the Emerald City home.

itemListElement.name: Lake, Old Growth Trees and the Beach Tour: Seattle's Beautiful Natural Spaces

name: Lake, Old Growth Trees and the Beach Tour: Seattle's Beautiful Natural Spaces
description:
Believe it or not, there is an old growth forest in Seattle! Let’s cruise the scenic shores of Lake Washington and learn the incredible history of how it was “re-plumbed” while on our way to Seward Park where we will have fantastic views of Mt. Rainier (if the mountain is out!). This park is an incredible gem holding one of only 2 old growth stands left in the city. The trail through the old growth is flat, less than 1 mile long and it’s ‘flip-flop accessible’. After that, lets get some locally roasted coffee and head to West Seattle to explore the beaches of Elliot Bay. This tour is mostly on foot, so wear your comfy shoes and appropriate weather gear.

With a max of 3 people, or 4 if you all know each other, this is a personal "best of Seattle" tour that explores the places you won't read about in most guidebooks. these are the places I take my friends and family when they come to visit, and I'd like to share them with you too. Come explore with a 30 year local!

itemListElement.name: Neighborhoods 101 Tour: great for newbies to build a mental map of the city!

name: Neighborhoods 101 Tour: great for newbies to build a mental map of the city!
description: Each neighborhood in Seattle has a unique feel, architectural style and social scene. Let’s take a ride and explore some of them! This tour focuses on the neighborhoods east, south and west of downtown. We will meander though the Volunteer Park neighborhood of Capitol Hill to see some of Seattle’s beautiful old Victorian style homes, then head to Madison Park and the shores of Lake Washington mid-century modern delights on our way to Seward Park, Columbia City, Beacon Hill, Georgetown and over to West Seattle. There are spectacular views all through this drive! If you’re a new resident of Seattle, or considering moving here, this is a great tour for you to start building a mental map of the feel of the city, guided by a resident of 30 years.

review.name: Excelente
review.reviewBody: Todo perfecto. Atención, local muy agradable y productos de primera calidad excelentemente cocinados. Una experiencia maravillosa

review.name: What a great experience
review.reviewBody: This tour was what made my trip to Seattle.  Lynn was really focused on showing me what I wanted to see, flexible, knowledgeable and totally enthusiastic about Seattle.  I was spoilt as I was the only one on the tour, but, I can't thank her enough for going out of her way to make sure that I had the best experience.  Even got to taste my first taco! I recommend this tour to anyone who wants to see the real Seattle. Long live Georgetown!!! There is so much to see and do and way more than just downtown.   Thanks Lynn.

review.name: A historically and culturally rich tour that takes you beyond what Seattle offers at first glance.
review.reviewBody: First, let me start off by saying this isn’t your typical hop on a bus and be monotonously drilled with average city trivia while you glaze over the city type of tour. This is personable; you and some friends with the owner of the tour on a journey soaking in the hidden treasures this city has to offer. Neighborhoods? Probably the most unique you’ll ever see. A culture in communities you can’t find else where. My view on Seattle has changed and in the most spectacular way. Coffee, food, cross walks, books you name it. Now I look at the ground beneath my feet and see a whole entire history below me. From streets, to buildings, to views there’s so much more going on than just those things. I’m new to the area and I always wonder “what the heck am I going to take my friends to do when the visit?” and it’s this. If you ever have anyone tell you they want to spend the day Seattle and see what it’s like, do your friends a favor and take them on this tour. I promise it’s better than moseying through pike place and the space needle acting like you know the joint. And if you’ve been here your whole life I’ll personally bet you 5 bucks you’d learn and see something you didn’t know existed.

itemListElement.name: Cannabis, Coffee and Dessert: Personal guided tour to unique Seattle culture!

name: Cannabis, Coffee and Dessert: Personal guided tour to unique Seattle culture!
description:
Marijuana is legal in Washington! Let me be your guide as we visit several different styles of legal cannabis shops and learn about the cannabis industry, laws and culture in the Emerald City. After we visit the shops, we will stop to get a locally-made beverage of your choice (we have many local brew pubs and obviously great coffee) then it’s your call! We can take a walk through an old growth forest, take a stroll on the beach, take a scenic drive around the city…you tell me what you like, and I’ll make it happen. We will finish with some fabulous local desserts to take care of those munchies.

With a max of 3 people, or 4 if you all know each other, this is a personal "best of Seattle" tour that explores the places you won't read about in most guidebooks. Come explore with a 30 year local!

itemListElement.name: West Seattle Tour: A world away and a state of mind!

name: West Seattle Tour: A world away and a state of mind!
description: West Seattle is the spit of land you can see when gazing west from downtown Seattle and Pike Place Market. It’s hard to imagine, but west Seattle has beaches and lovely little shops along the waterfront with views of Bainbridge Island and the Olympic Mountains. Home to the best record store in the city where Pearl Jam once played and one of the last stands of old growth trees in Seattle, West Seattle is a world unto itself. The city skyline view is iconic from "the west side", perfect for photos to make your friends back home wish they were with us! These are the places I bring my friends and family when they visit, let's explore them together.

itemListElement.name: Roll the Dice Tour: Throw caution to the wind, dealer's choice tour!

name: Roll the Dice Tour: Throw caution to the wind, dealer's choice tour!
description:
On any given day in Seattle, there are experiences to be had that cannot be scheduled…

Maybe its a super windy day, a rare and perfect time for visiting the Sound Garden! Perhaps the resident orcas will decide to swim in Elliott Bay, so lets go see them. Maybe Jeff B. is having a BBQ at the beach house, so let’s hop a ferry and head west for a few hours! 

This tour is a dealer’s choice tour, where you allow me to host a “best of the day” adventure. You can tell me what you are interested in doing, and I’ll craft a fun outing for us.

NOTE: I chose Capitol Hill as a step on the tour, but the rest of the tour could be anywhere :-)

name: Duwamish Indians - Native Seattle Culture
description:
The Duwamish Tribe in Seattle is a small but strong tribe, still fighting for their rights for federal recognition. Visit their Long House and park, both along the Duwamish River. See downtown statues of Chief Seattle, and visit a Pike Place Market shop dedicated to Native American art.

Our tour is a great way to learn more about the history of local Indians on Puget Sound.

itemListElement.name: House of Smith Jet City Winery

name: House of Smith Jet City Winery

itemListElement.name: 3 Days in Olympic National Park from Seattle: Silent Forest - Hoh Rainforest

name: 3 Days in Olympic National Park from Seattle: Silent Forest - Hoh Rainforest
description:
A first-rate adventure in our favorite 1,100 square mile national treasure – spend time on foot in our favorite places in Olympic National Park! Our team built this tour to reconnect with natural silence in powerful landscapes; Olympic National Park is recognized as likely the quietest place remaining in North America. We’re out to pursue the tranquility that has been part of how humans have experienced the world for millennia – as we believe silence is being rapidly eradicated in our modern age.

For three refreshing days, leave behind the bustle of the city to unwind in the beauty of Olympic National Park's pristine beaches, rivers, forests, and mountains. Follow in the footsteps of Roosevelt elk and black tail deer, discover tumbling waterfalls that feed into the crystalline Hoh River, decompress under a canopy of green as moss-draped Big-Leaf Maples spread upwards overhead.

This tour is all-inclusive, we'll take care of the details.

review.name: Well worth the $.
review.reviewBody: We hadone Week in the Seattle area - we wanted to see Mt Ranier and Olympic National Parks.  We did a day trip to Ranier and then three days in Olympic by booking both trips one right after the other. This worked well, felt efficient, and we did not feel crowded nor uncomfortable sharing the experience with others.  Both guides were great, food was very good, the lodging in Olympic was excellent.  Would do it this way again, highly recommend.

review.name: Worth it
review.reviewBody: I had an amazing time on my three day vanishing silence Olympic National Park tour lead by Evan S! Each day was filled with so many different places, I really felt like I got to experience the entire area. Evan was so knowledgeable and friendly and really enhanced the trip by all the background and context he could provide for everything. You can tell he is passionate about the area and does his research. Additionally, the lodge we stayed at was very nice, and the food provided was surprisingly good. I knew the company can accommodate dietary restrictions but I wasn’t sure what the vegan options would be. Turns out they were very thoughtful and delicious. Really I can’t recommend this tour enough! Thank you Evan S and Evergreen escapes!

review.name: Olympic National park and hoh rainforest
review.reviewBody: This was a wonderful tour. Saw some incredible sites in Olympic National park, had some great hikes and views. Evan S was an incredible and knowledgeable guide and really helped us engage with nature and all the different sites. It felt like we got to do and see so much in such a relatively short time. Definitely a tour worth doing!

review.name: Olympic National Park Tour
review.reviewBody: This trip was Amazing! Sarah, our tour guide was super knowledgeable, nice and accommodating! She went the extra mile to make our trip special! The Olympic National Forest is truly a national treasure!

review.name: Amazing!!
review.reviewBody: The trip was amazing! Each day was well-planned out and I felt all our needs were taken care of. I am gluten free and dairy free and they were able to accommodate without a problem. Our guide, Sean, was incredibly knowledgeable and I learned a ton about everything we were seeing. I would definitely do a tour with Evergreen Escapes again!

review.name: 3 Ecosystems in 3 Memorable Days
review.reviewBody: My husband, 18-year old son, and I went on the 3-day Olympic National Park Silent Forest tour.  Our guide Sean was amazingly knowledgeable about everything to do with the park's plants and animals and history.   The must-do is the pre-dawn chorus at the Hoh Rainforest with Matt and Sean.  To hear the rainforest as it woke to the sunrise was amazing.  Matt and Sean's insights about the park helped us to better see, hear, and appreciate nature in a new way.  A few favorites included our picnic at Lake Crescent, sun sets at the beach, the view from atop Blue Mountain, our hobo dinner, smores around the bonfire, the tree of life, and the square inch of silence.   A few surprises included Sean pulling to the side of the road and taking us to an unmarked path that led to the most beautiful waterfall; a "sunny" day in the rainforest, and how cheery we all could be at 3:30am.  We were not fans of the mobile chalets, we prefer flushable toilets and hot showers, but we loved ending our days relaxing around the fire, looking up at the stars, and listening to the ocean in the distance.  Sean was a great guide and took care of everything down to the smallest details including snacks on the trail, bug spray, challenging our adventurous teen-age son, and entertaining us with riddles on the drive back to the ferry.  This was our first trip with Evergreen Escapes and we would definitely use them again.   A big shout out to Sean and Matt - Thanks for a great time and we will look for more "quiet" places.  ---The Family from Chicago
